ownedComment.body:
The Enable command is used to transition the support system from the DisabledState to the ParkedState.
The Enable attribute must be TRUE for the transition to occur.

The Disable command is used to transition the support system from the ParkedState to the DisabledState OR from the ParkedEngineeringState to the DisabledState.
The Disable attribute must be TRUE for the transition to occur.

The Standby command is used to transition the support system from the DisabledState to the StandbyState.
The Standby attribute must be TRUE for the transition to occur.

The Start command is used to transition the support system from the StandbyState to the DisabledState.
The Start attribute must be TRUE for the transition to occur. The SettingsToApply attribute defines which settings to apply to the application.

The DetailedState event is used to publish a detailed state transition (OfflineState, StandbyState, DisabledState, EnabledState, FaultState, ParkedState, RaisingState, ActiveState, LoweringState, ParkedEngineeringState, RaisingEngineeringState, ActiveEngineeringState, LoweringEngineeringState).
The Timestamp attribute defines when the state transition occurred. The DetailedState attribute is the enumerated value indicating the detailed state the control system is currently in.

The ErrorCode event is used to publish error codes when transitioning to FaultState.
The Timestamp attribute defines when the error code was published. The ErrorCode attribute is the primary error code as defined by LTS-441. The DetailedErrorCode attribute is used to define a specific condition for the ErrorCode.
Example: ErrorCode 6102 indicates an error with the displacement sensors. DetailedErrorCode 11 indicates a response timeout error.

The SummaryState event is used to publish a summary state transition (OfflineState, StandbyState, DisabledState, EnabledState, FaultState).
The Timestamp attribute defines when the state transition occurred. The SummaryState attribute is the enumerated value indicating the summary state the control system is currently in.

mdElement.text: Primary responsibility is to generate ICommands utilizing the SAL interface.
Utilize the command pattern to simplify command execution.
Queue commands for execution to prevent multiple commands from executing at the same time.
Responsible for creating the state object and calling the correct command Primary responsibility is to join the concept of state with functionality (model).
Responsible for defining what (if anything) is done in a given state for a given command. The state uses the model to perform actions.
Responsible for providing high level functionality. The model should be state independent.
Responsible for using SAL to inform the outside world about the state of the system and provide telemetry for processing.

NOTES:

  • Following types are NOT supported: wchar, wstring & long double.
  • For XML Schema properties: Alias, EFDB_Name or EFDB_Topic, No embedded spaces.
  • For XML Schema property: eventFileRefType, URL should be a well formed URI,
    • e.g. urm://[ip address]/some/path/file.type
      • urm is a curl compatible source, e.g. ftp, http, file, etc.
  • XML Schema property: MIME_TYPE, should be a valid mime-type
    • In "/etc/mime.types" or "/usr/share/applications/defaults.list" on most Linux systems
  • The total number of bytes used in a topic must be < 65K.
  • The following reserved words SHOULD NOT appear as names, Aliases, etc:
    • abstract, any, attribute, boolean, case, char, component, const consumes, context, custom, dec, default, double, emits, enum, eventype, exception, factory, false, finder, fixed, float, getraises, home, home, import, in, inout, interface, limit, local, long, module, multiple, native, object, octet, oneway, out, primarykey, private, provides, public, publishes, raises, readonly, sequence, setraises, short, string, struct, supports, switch, true, truncatable, typedef, typeid, typeprefix, union, unsigned, uses, valuebase, valuetype, void, wchar, wstring
char arrays NOT ALLOWED (i.e. XML Schema property COUNT = 1)
string arrays NOT ALLOWED (i.e. XML Schema property COUNT = 1)
